----------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Testing evaluation:-
    --------------------

    This was tested on an A500 with various memory configurations,
    the same A500 switched to 1MB Chip Ram and emulating WB2 using
    the A500+ emulator, an A600 with various memory configurations,
    the same A600 emulating WB3 with various memory configurations,
    an A1200 with various memory configurations, and a similar A1200
    with a Turbo LC accelerator board and an '030 with 34MB of ram
    thanks to Laurence J Greatorex, and also to Bob Eva for testing on his
    A1200 setup, with a total of 10MB of memory, and to Nathan Shepherd
    with an absolutely standard A500 without a mouse.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Next project:-
    --------------

    This will be ~TestGear4A.lha~ and ~TestGear4A.readme~ and is a Digital
    Storage Oscilloscope. The Oscilloscope will be built in stages and
    requires a Standard A1200 with a second floppy disk drive as a minimum
    to run. It will probably NOT work with fast accelerator cards.

    This, and all future projects, will be in the ~hard/test~ drawer
    in the AMINET archive.

